                  </hi>. I am sixteen years old, and live with my grandmother, the prosecutrix, at 9, Richard-street, Woolwich—I recollect seeing the prisoner on 11th February, about 2 o'clock in the day—I saw him snatch two boots from the doorway of my grandmother's shop—I ran after him and caught him—he had the boots beneath his coat—I said, "Give me those</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="186102250069"></xptr>
               <p>boots"—he said, "No I won't, I shall be taken up"—I gave him into custody—these (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>) are the boots—they are my grandmother's.</p>
